snippet.textDisplay:
Top Questions:
1. Why not build full-scale?
It would cost more than buying a real one -- remember, mass production is the only reason cars cost less than 100k. If I had to guess, I'd say the real prototype Cybertrucks Elon revealed probably cost 500k-1M each.
2. Where are the _____?
It's not done yet. There will be windows, a tow hitch, lights, bumpers, wheel fenders, the interior, an iPad dash and more.
3. Are you sure it's halfscale?
We divided the dimensions of the real thing by half. It's half the width, half the length, half the height -- but that also means it's only 1/8th the volume. To me, that's half scale. To model toy companies, maybe not. I dunno.
4. Hurry up and finish it!
Follow us @thehacksmith on Instagram for updates between videos.
5. Powerloader?
It's on hold while we set up the new facility, follow our vlog channel for updates! It will return soon.
